---
title: Cajun-Spiced Chicken & Mushroom Cavatappi with Creamy Tomato Sauce, Green Pepper & Scallions
description: Get ready for a rich, luscious vegan pasta dinner! Coconut milk may sound like an odd addition to your go-to red sauce, but trust us, it’s what gives our vegan veggie-packed pasta its next-level creaminess. You’ll start by sautéing mushrooms and green pepper, adding scallion and garlic, then creating a creamy spiced roux right in the pan for maximum Cajun flavor. Crushed tomatoes and coconut milk bring it all together for a sauce so delicious that cavatappi pasta can’t resist hopping right in. If you’re feeling the bayou in you, finish with hot sauce and let the good times roll!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vegan-cajun-spiced-mushroom-cavatappi-7384603e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64ca997ad1320bb7c7146ee5.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cajun-spiced-chicken-mushroom-cavatappi-64ca997ad1320bb7c7146ee5
time required: 25 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 950 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 105 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 800 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Core and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir in garlic, scallion whites, @flour{1%tablespoon}, @blackening spices{1%tablespoon}, and another large drizzle of oil; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Add @diced tomatoes{14%ounce} to same pan and cook, stirring, until jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @coconut milk{1}(shaking first), @mushroom stock concentrate{2%unit}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water.

Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir drained cavatappi and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} into pan with sauce; toss to coat.

Add chicken to sauce along with cavatappi.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and drizzle with as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.